Basic User Stories

As a logged-in user (any role with the add_expenses capability), I want to be able to quickly add new expenses with the amount, date, and a description, so that I can keep track of my spending.
As a logged-in user, I want to choose from a list of predefined expense categories (e.g., food, travel, entertainment) so that I can categorize my expenses.
As a logged-in user, I want to create my own custom expense categories so that I can organize my expenses in a way that makes sense to me.
As a logged-in user, I want to view a list of all my expenses, sorted by date, so that I can see where my money is going.
As a logged-in user, I want to be able to edit or delete an existing expense in case I make a mistake or need to update the information.
Group/Organization User Stories

As a logged-in user (any role with the create_groups capability), I want to create a new group so that I can track shared expenses with other users.
As a group administrator (role with the manage_group_members capability), I want to invite other users to join my group so that we can track shared expenses.
As a member of a group, I want to be able to see the expenses added by other group members so that we have a shared view of our finances.
As a group administrator, I want to be able to assign roles and permissions to group members (e.g., "viewer," "editor") so that I can control who has access to modify expenses.
Admin User Stories

As an administrator, I want to configure the plugin settings, including which user roles have permission to add expenses, create groups, and manage group members.
As an administrator, I want to be able to view and manage all expenses added by all users.
As an administrator, I want to be able to create, edit, and delete predefined expense categories that are available to all users.
Advanced User Stories

As a user, I want to generate reports of my expenses over a specific period, so that I can analyze my spending habits.
As a user, I want to set a budget for different categories and receive alerts if I exceed my budget.
As a user, I want to upload receipts or images for each expense, so that I have a visual record of my spending

These user stories provide a good starting point.

Now you have a clear understanding of the user needs.
